97297f9e3dc2e762e0ed5dda0e/contracts/Auctions/DutchAuction.sol:263-285","0x4c4564a1fe775d97297f9e3dc2e762e0ed5dda0e/contracts/Auctions/DutchAuction.sol:521-537","0x4c4564a1fe775d97297f9e3dc2e762e0ed5dda0e/contracts/Auctions/DutchAuction.sol:545-560","0x4c4564a1fe775d97297f9e3dc2e762e0ed5dda0e/contracts/Auctions/DutchAuction.sol:606-613"],"claim":"commitEth, setDocument, setDocuments, removeDocument, setList, and setAuctionWallet lack nonReentrant modifier while commitTokensFrom, withdrawTokens, cancelAuction, and finalize have it.","impact":"Functions without reentrancy protection are vulnerable to reentrant calls that could manipulate state variables or cause unexpected behavior.","paths":["1. Attacker calls commitEth in a reentrant manner","2. Attacker calls setAuctionWallet within the same transaction"]},{"id":"F-004","severity":"High","confidence":"medium","title":"Division by zero in price calculation functions","locations":["0x4c4564a1fe775d97297f9e3dc2e762e0ed5dda0e/contracts/Auctions/DutchAuction.sol:204-207","0x4c4564a1fe775d97297f9e3dc2e762e0ed5dda0e/contracts/Auctions/DutchAuction.sol:364-370","0x4c4564a1fe775d97297f9e3dc2e762e0ed5dda0e/contracts/Auctions/DutchAuction.sol:355-357"],"claim":"tokenPrice(), calculateCommitment(), and totalTokensCommitted() can revert due to division by zero if clearingPrice() returns 0 (when minimumPrice is 0).","impact":"Auction becomes unusable if clearing price is calculated as 0, causing all calls to these view functions to revert and breaking integration with off-chain tools.","paths":["1. Admin initializes auction with minimumPrice = 0 (or minimum price calculated results in 0)","2. Any user calling tokenPrice(), calculateCommitment(), or totalTokensCommitted() gets division by zero error"]},{"id":"F-005","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Deprecated Solidity version 0.6.12","locations":["0x4c4564a1fe775d97297f9e3dc2e762e0ed5dda0e/contracts/Auctions/DutchAuction.sol:1"],"claim":"Contract uses Solidity 0.6.12 which is an older version with known issues and has reached end-of-life.","impact":"Using deprecated compiler versions may introduce security vulnerabilities that have been fixed in newer versions. Code may be incompatible with modern tooling.","paths":[]},{"id":"F-006","severity":"Medium","confidence":"medium","title":"Outdated .transfer() pattern for ETH transfers","locations":["0x4c4564a1fe775d97297f9e3dc2e762e0ed5dda0e/contracts/Utils/SafeTransfer.sol:28"],"claim":"_tokenPayment uses .transfer() which only provides 2300 gas (EIP-1884), while _safeTokenPayment uses .call() which is the recommended pattern.","impact":"ETH transfers via _tokenPayment may fail for contracts that require more than 2300 gas, causing the transaction to revert.","paths":[]},{"id":"F-007","severity":"Medium","confidence":"low","title":"Comment and code discrepancy for finalizeTimeExpired","locations":["0x4c4564a1fe775d97297f9e3dc2e762e0ed5dda0e/contracts/Auctions/DutchAuction.sol:404-408"],"claim":"The comment states '14 days' but the code uses '7 days' (block.timestamp + 7 days).","impact":"Confusing for integrators who rely on documentation. May lead to incorrect assumptions about auction finalization timing.","paths":[]},{"id":"F-008","severity":"Low","confidence":"high","title":"Wallet address can trigger finalization","locations":["0x4c4564a1fe775d97297f9e3dc2e762e0ed5dda0e/contracts/Auctions/DutchAuction.sol:463-469"],"claim":"The wallet address (payment recipient) is allowed to call finalize(), creating a conflict of interest.","impact":"Wallet owner can finalize the auction themselves, potentially before the intended timeout, to gain early access to funds.","paths":[]},{"id":"F-009","severity":"Low","confidence":"medium","title":"IERC20 interface requires permit which many tokens lack","locations":["0x4c4564a1fe775d97297f9e3dc2e762e0ed5dda0e/contracts/interfaces/IERC20.sol:15-23","0x4c4564a1fe775d97297f9e3dc2e762e0ed5dda0e/contracts/Utils/BoringBatchable.sol:52-63"],"claim":"The IERC20 interface includes permit() function (EIP-2612) which many tokens do not implement, and BoringBatchable.permitToken() calls this on any token.","impact":"Contracts using BoringBatchable.permitToken() will revert when used with tokens that don't support permit(), causing transaction failures.","paths":[]},{"id":"F-010","severity":"Low","confidence":"medium","title":"Missing validation for pointList contract","locations":["0x4c4564a1fe775d97297f9e3dc2e762e0ed5dda0e/contracts/Auctions/DutchAuction.sol:555-560"],"claim":"_setList does not verify that the pointList contract implements the IPointList interface.","impact":"If a non-conforming contract is set as pointList, calls to IPointList(pointList).hasPoints() will revert, breaking auction participation.","paths":["1. Admin sets a non-IPointList contract as pointList","2. Users cannot commit to auction due to revert in hasPoints call"]}]
