 donated.","impact":"Any external account can cheaply and permissionlessly deny service to the recovery flow, blocking liquidation of legitimately recovered WBTC/USDC/USDT/WETH proceeds as well. Since the contract has no token rescue or dust-clearing path, the griefing balance can persist indefinitely and strand future recoveries.","paths":["An attacker transfers 1 wei of DAI to `FlawVerifier`","A caller invokes `executeOnOpportunity()`","`_swapTokenToEth(DAI)` observes `bal > 0` and calls the Uniswap V2 router with `amountIn = 1`","The swap computes zero ETH output for that tiny amount and reverts, bubbling the failure up","The whole transaction reverts, so no bounty sweep or liquidation can complete until more DAI is added"],"round":5,"source_agents":["codex"]},{"id":"F-007","severity":"Medium","confidence":"medium","title":"Profit check can be satisfied with preloaded token balances instead of new recovery profit","locations":["FlawVerifier.sol:50","FlawVerifier.sol:54","FlawVerifier.sol:58","FlawVerifier.sol:63","FlawVerifier.sol:96"],"claim":"`executeOnOpportunity()` snapshots only the contract's native ETH balance as `initialBalance`, then counts any pre-existing WETH or supported ERC20s already sitting in the contract after they are unwrapped or swapped during the same call. A caller can therefore donate roughly `0.1 ether` worth of WETH, or enough swappable WBTC/USDC/USDT/DAI, before invoking `executeOnOpportunity()` and make the final `Insufficient profit` check pass even if `_sweepBounties()` recovered nothing.","impact":"This defeats the verifier's only profitability gate. A third party can use their own tokens to force otherwise unprofitable sweep attempts, causing the contract to run the full external `startPool`/`endPool` mutation sequence at arbitrary times even when no new value was recovered. If the underlying opportunity is timing-sensitive or one-shot, that can consume it or leave later legitimate recovery attempts with nothing to claim.","paths":["Transfer at least `0.1 ether` worth of WETH, or enough supported swappable tokens, to `FlawVerifier`","Call `executeOnOpportunity()`","The function measures `initialBalance` using only native ETH, then unwraps or swaps the donated token inventory into ETH","The final `require(address(this).balance >= initialBalance + 0.1 ether)` passes even if `_sweepBounties()` produced no new proceeds"],"round":6,"source_agents":["codex"]},{"id":"F-009","severity":"Medium","confidence":"medium","title":"USDC or USDT blacklisting can permanently DoS all future recoveries","locations":["FlawVerifier.sol:55","FlawVerifier.sol:56","FlawVerifier.sol:96","FlawVerifier.sol:103"],"claim":"The contract must successfully swap any positive USDC or USDT balance through Uniswap, but it has no skip path, rescue path, or per-token isolation if those centralized stablecoins refuse transfers. If this contract is ever blacklisted or transfer-blocked by USDC or USDT while holding a positive balance, `_swapTokenToEth()` reverts and aborts the entire `executeOnOpportunity()` transaction.","impact":"A single blocked USDC or USDT balance prevents liquidation of every other recovered asset as well, because the whole recovery transaction reverts before completion. Since the contract has no token rescue mechanism, subsequent bounty proceeds can remain stranded behind one centralized-token failure mode indefinitely.","paths":["`_sweepBounties()` or a direct transfer leaves a positive USDC or USDT balance in `FlawVerifier`","The token issuer blacklists this contract or otherwise causes transfers from it to fail","A later `executeOnOpportunity()` call reaches `_swapTokenToEth(USDC)` or `_swapTokenToEth(USDT)`","The router transfer fails and the full recovery transaction reverts, blocking liquidation of all assets"],"round":6,"source_agents":["codex"]}],"rejected_candidates":[]}
